{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh noodles into it. Cover with boiling water and set aside.","Place 50 g of the miso paste, sake, mirin and brown sugar into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>4 min\/120°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer glaze into a ceramic dish and set aside to cool. Do not clean mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with aluminium foil and set aside.","Place oil and garlic into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, place salmon into reserved glaze and turn to coat.","Drain noodles using simmering basket. Add drained noodles, hot water, mushrooms, soy sauce, salt, pepper and remaining 2 teaspoons miso paste to mixing bowl and cook <nobr>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, transfer salmon onto prepared baking tray and bake for 7 minutes (200°C). Set remaining glaze aside.","Add bok choy to mixing bowl and cook <nobr>4 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove salmon from oven. Turn oven setting to grill and carefully move oven rack to upper part of oven. Brush salmon with remaining reserved glaze and place under pre-heated grill for 2-3 minutes, until surface blackens and salmon is cooked to your liking. Flake salmon into bite-size pieces.","Divide soup between serving bowls and top with salmon. Garnish with spring onions\/shallots and sprinkle with black sesame seeds (optional) to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g dried instant noodles (see Tip)","boiling water, for soaking","50 g shiro (white) miso paste, plus extra 2 teaspoons","50 g sake","50 g mirin","40 g brown sugar","20 g peanut oil","1 garlic clove, cut into thin slices","4 boneless skinless salmon fillets (approx. 800 g total)","800 g hot water","100 g fresh shiitake mushrooms, cut into thin slices (5 mm)","20 g soy sauce","½ tsp salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","150 g bok choy, trimmed and cut into pieces (4 cm) with stalks separated","2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and thinly sliced, for garnishing","black sesame seeds, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r335072","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-R7XmhgQTzMw\/XZMz1y4jPuI\/AAAAAAAAa18\/Pkvth1wpSw4rcKMMAwlHCn2e43Eh5EYRgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lDtnuT6U6RdQvfiS.png","title":"Miso salmon broth","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"50.8 g","fat":"40.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"39.4 g","calories":"3065.4 kJ \/ 729.8 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, ceramic dish, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), aluminium foil, serving bowls, pastry brush, oven, oven grill","hintsAndTricks":["We used a dried sweet potato noodle for this recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","40m","4 portions"]}